page.title: 12Sywell Rectory.
page.content: The Incumbent of Sywell Church and its sister church, St. Nicholas in Overstone, lives in a Regency Rectory set in two and a half acres of ground a short walk from Sywell Church. Each summer, the Rectory Garden Party is held in the grounds. There are usually a variety of stalls and games to play and refreshments can be enjoyed at tables on the lawns overlooking the magnificent countryside. It is an afternoon much enjoyed by those who attend. Muntjac deer, rabbits, moles and foxes are frequent visitors to the grounds as are swallows in the summer.
